               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-241-person1333">
                  THOMAS 
                  ROBERTS
               <interp inst="t18260406-241-person1333" type="surname" value="ROBERTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-241-person1333" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-241-person1333" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 24th of February, about a quarter before seven o'clock, I saw the prisoner, and two other persons, at Messrs. Harris' shop - I saw him take the two half-handkerchiefs from the inside of the shop door, and put them into his pocket - I followed him, and took him about three or four yards from the door - Bertraun, who was with me, found them in his pocket - his companions did not go with him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-241-person1334">
                  ANGELIOUS 
                  BERTRAUN
               <interp inst="t18260406-241-person1334" type="surname" value="BERTRAUN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-241-person1334" type="given" value="ANGELIOUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-241-person1334" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was in company with Roberts - I did not see the handkerchief taken, but I took the prisoner, and found the two half-handkerchiefs in his coat.</p>
               <p>THOMAS HARRIS. I am in partnership with my father<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182604060098"></xptr>Edward Harris - we live in <placeName id="t18260406-241-crimeloc1307">King-street, Soho</placeName>
